## 3. Target Audience & Searcher Profile

The primary searcher is a first-time renter or someone re-entering the rental market after several years, aged 22-35, who understands they need to find an apartment but does not yet know the full sequence of what is required. They are in the **early discovery stage** of the renter journey: they have a reason to move (new job, leaving home, relocating) but have not yet started searching or prepared documents. Their specific problem is that they do not know what landlords require, what the qualification standards are, or how the process flows from search to move-in. Based on the SERP analysis, they expect a numbered process guide with clear stages, practical document checklists, and honest information about what they will need financially before they start.

